Name: AccountCurrencyCode
Notes: The currency of the Customer account.

Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AccountTimeZoneId
Notes: Name of the timezone selected for the Customer account. For example: "(GMT-05:00) Eastern Time". This field does not reflect the current state of daylight saving time for the timezone.

Name: ActiveViewCpm
Notes: Average cost of viewable impressions (ActiveViewImpressions).

Name: ActiveViewImpressions
Notes: How often your ad has become viewable on a Display Network site.

Name: AdGroupAdDisapprovalReasons
Notes:
List of disapproval reasons for the ad.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: AdGroupId
Notes: The ID of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupName
Notes: The name of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: Status of the ad group.

Name: AdNetworkType1
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Search Network
CONTENT / Display Network
Notes: First level network type.

Name: AdNetworkType2
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Google search
SEARCH_PARTNERS / Search partners
CONTENT / Display Network
Notes: Second level network type (includes search partners).

Name: AdType
Enum Values:
DEPRECATED_AD / Other
IMAGE_AD / Image ad
PRODUCT_AD / Product listing ad
TEMPLATE_AD / Display ad
TEXT_AD / Text ad
THIRD_PARTY_REDIRECT_AD / Third party ad
DYNAMIC_SEARCH_AD / Dynamic search ad
CALL_ONLY_AD / Call only ad
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: The type of the Ad.

Name: AdvertiserExperimentSegmentationBin
Enum Values:
OUTSIDE_OF_EXPERIMENT / outside experiment
CONTROL / control
EXPERIMENT / experiment
Notes: Experiment group of the impressions.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AveragePageviews
Notes: Average number of pages viewed per session. Imported from Google Analytics.

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers.

Name: AverageTimeOnSite
Notes: Total duration of all sessions (in seconds) / number of sessions. Imported from Google Analytics.

Name: BounceRate
Notes: Percentage of clicks where the user only visited a single page on your site, formatted as "x.xx%". Imported from Google Analytics.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: The status of the Campaign.

Name: ClickAssistedConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign triggered assist clicks.

Name: ClickAssistedConversions
Notes: The total number of conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign contributed one or more assist clicks.

Name: ClickAssistedConversionsOverLastClickConversions
Display Name: Click Assisted Conv. / Last Click Conv.
Notes: The total number of conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign received assist clicks divided by the total number of conversions for which it triggered the last click.

Name: ClickConversionRate
Notes: The number of converted clicks divided by your total clicks that can be tracked to a conversion. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: ClickConversionRateSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ClickConversionRate.

Name: ClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in Clicks.

Name: ClickType
Enum Values:
URL_CLICKS / Headline
CALLS / Phone calls
OTHER / Other
PRODUCT_EXTENSION_CLICKS / Product plusbox offer
SITELINKS / Sitelink
PRODUCT_LISTING_AD_CLICKS / Product listing ad
GET_DIRECTIONS / Driving direction
OFFER_PRINTS / Print offer
BREADCRUMBS / Breadcrumbs
CALL_TRACKING / Manually dialed phone calls
MOBILE_CALL_TRACKING / Mobile phone calls
LOCATION_EXPANSION / Get location details
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: The Impressions field will reflect how often the ad was served with that click type available. Since ads can serve with multiple click types displayed, impressions may be double counted and the totals may not be accurate.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ConversionCategoryName
Notes: Not compatible with non-conversion stats (AverageCpc, Clicks, etc). Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.  Values: "Other", "View of a key page", "Purchase/Sale", "Signup", "Lead"

Name: ConversionManyPerClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ConversionManyPerClick.

Name: ConversionRateManyPerClick
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: ConversionRateManyPerClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ConversionRateManyPerClick.

Name: ConversionTrackerId
Notes: ID of the conversion tracker.

Name: ConversionTypeName
Notes: Not compatible with non-conversion stats (AverageCpc, Clicks, etc).  Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions.

Name: ConversionsManyPerClick
Notes: This column reports total conversions, across all the conversion actions you're tracking. How you've chosen to count your conversions (unique or all) affects the number shown in this column.

Name: ConvertedClicks
Notes: The number of clicks that converted within your chosen conversion window.

Name: ConvertedClicksSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ConvertedClicks.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period. Other costs such as cost-per-call aren't included. For a sum of all costs, use the TotalCost column.

Name: CostPerConversionManyPerClick
Notes: Total cost divided by your total conversions.

Name: CostPerConversionManyPerClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CostPerConversionManyPerClick.

Name: CostPerConvertedClick
Notes: Cost divided by your total converted clicks.

Name: CostPerConvertedClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CostPerConvertedClick.

Name: CostSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in Cost.

Name: CpcSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CPC.

Name: CpmSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CPM.

Name: CreativeApprovalStatus
Enum Values:
APPROVED / approved
FAMILY_SAFE / approved
NON_FAMILY_SAFE / approved (non family)
PORN / approved (adult)
UNCHECKED / pending review
DISAPPROVED / disapproved
Notes: Approval status of the ad.

Name: CreativeDestinationUrl
Notes: Destination URL of the ad.

Name: CreativeFinalAppUrls
Notes:
List of final app URLs of the ad.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: CreativeFinalMobileUrls
Notes:
List of final mobile URLs of the ad.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: CreativeFinalUrls
Notes:
List of final URLs of the ad.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: CreativeTrackingUrlTemplate
Notes: Tracking template of the ad.

Name: CreativeUrlCustomParameters
Notes: List of custom parameters of the ad.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: CtrSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CTR.

Name: CustomerDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek
Enum Values:
MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday
Notes: The name of the day of the week, e.g., "Monday".

Name: Description1
Notes: Line 1 description of the Ad.

Name: Description2
Notes: Line 2 description of the Ad.

Name: Device
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
DESKTOP / Computers
HIGH_END_MOBILE / Mobile devices with full browsers
TABLET / Tablets with full browsers
Notes: Device type where the impression was shown.

Name: DevicePreference
Notes: Platform ID of the device preference. You can look up the corresponding name and other information in the Platforms reference.

Name: DisplayUrl
Notes: Display URL of the Ad.

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: GmailForwards
Notes: The number of times your ad was forwarded to someone else as a message.

Name: GmailSaves
Notes: The number of times someone has saved your Gmail ad to their inbox as a message.

Name: GmailSecondaryClicks
Notes: The number of clicks to your landing page on the expanded state of Gmail ads.

Name: Headline
Notes: The ad headline for a TextAd. For other ad types such as TemplateAds, this field will contain a string representation of the key attributes of the ad.

Name: Id
Notes: ID of the main object of this row.

Name: ImageAdUrl
Notes: Prefix this value with "https://tpc.googlesyndication.com/pageadimg/imgad?id=" to get the full URL.

Name: ImageCreativeName
Notes: Name for the image ad.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversionValue
Notes: Total value of all conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversions
Notes: Total number of conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions prior to the last click.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversionsOverLastClickConversions
Display Name: Impr. Assisted Conv. / Last Click Conv.
Notes: Total number of conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions divided by the total number of conversions for which this object triggered the last click.

Name: ImpressionSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in Impressions.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: IsNegative
Notes: Indicates if the criterion for this row is a negative (exclusion) criterion.

Name: KeywordId
Notes: In the Ad Performance Report this field contains the ID of the criterion that triggered the ad, segmenting the report and preventing zero impressions. The ID can be for any type of criterion, including placements, verticals, etc. Cross-reference with the Criteria Report to determine the criteria type and details.

Name: LabelIds
Notes:
List of label IDs for the main object of this row.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: Labels
Notes:
List of label names for the main object of this row.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: MonthOfYear
Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September
OCTOBER / October
NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: PercentNewVisitors
Notes: Percentage of first-time sessions (from people who had never visited your site before), formatted as "x.xx%". Imported from Google Analytics.

Name: PositionSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ad position.

Name: PrimaryCompanyName
Notes: Company name of the account.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: SharedSetName
Notes: The name of the SharedSet.

Name: Slot
Enum Values:
SearchRhs / Google search: Side
SearchTop / Google search: Top
SearchOther / Google search: Other
Content / Google Display Network
AfsTop / Search partners: Top
AfsOther / Search partners: Other
Unknown /
Notes: The position of the Ad.

Name: Status
Enum Values:
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
DISABLED / disabled
Notes: The status of the main object in this row. For example, in a Campaign Performance Report this will be the status of each row's Campaign. In an Ad Group Performance Report this will be the status of each row's AdGroup.

Name: Trademarks
Notes:
Trademarks related to this object's approval status.
List elements are delimited by the semicolon character (;)

Name: ValuePerConversionManyPerClick
Notes: The total value of all conversions divided by the total number of conversions.

Name: ValuePerConvertedClick
Notes: The total value of all conversions divided by the total number of converted clicks.

Name: ViewThroughConversions
Notes: The value, on average, of your total estimated conversions.

Name: ViewThroughConversionsSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ViewThroughConversions.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
